Author: NightDream
Title: [ANN] TRAXION - TRANSITIONS YOU TO A CRYPTO-READY SOCIETY
Body: TraXion crowdfunding service GavaGives signs partnership with Coins.ph    TraXion is proud to announce that GavaGives — the philanthropy platform powering TraXion’s charitable crowdfunding service — has signed a partnership with Coins.ph, Southeast Asia’s leading digital wallet app. The partnership will be used to bring attention to leading Philippine charity site GavaGives.com, and how it is being incorporated into TraXion and other similar e-wallets.  Similar to TraXion, Coins.ph primarily delivers financial services over mobile to more than 300 million unbanked people in Southeast Asia, enabling them to make cash deposits and withdrawals at more than 10 thousand participating retail locations. Other services include bill payments, mobile top-ups and remittances. It also grants access to online shopping at over 100 thousand retailers that accept digital currency.  Now, whenever someone uses their Coins.ph app to donate money to a charitable cause, the user can go to Bills Payment and look for the Donate section. This section houses GavaGives’ reputable NGO partners that anyone can support.  GavaGives has over 120 NGO partners, and has helped raise over $1 million USD for various causes in just the past year alone. All donors on GavaGives are automatically given a “reputation score” via blockchain smart contracts, with the highest-performing ones gaining prominence on the site. Through GavaGive’s data-sharing deal with Coins.ph, making charitable donations will now be just as easy as it is with the TraXion wallet.  But the real value is not just ease of use. It’s trust. Because the NGOs are all ranked on a blockchain database, there is finally true transparency in charitable donations. This means that money can be donated with the full knowledge of where it is going and how it is being used. This is huge. Traditionally, charities have been far too open to fraud abuse, with almost half of all fraud cases going unreported for fear of losing future donations.  “Charity fraud is not only about NGOs losing donations. It has massive knock-on effects in terms of creating public distrust toward charities, resulting in greatly reduced donations overall. Meaning the needy lose out on assistance that would otherwise come to them if corruption did not exist. We aim to end that,” said TraXion CEO Ann Cuisa.  Our team at TraXion envisions a future free from charity fraud. And we’re giving a big shout out to Coins.ph for also embracing this goal.  https://medium.com/traxion-tech/traxion-crowdfunding-service-gavagives-signs-partnership-with-coins-ph-ee80b958a2e0

Author: sv.alyona
Title: [ANN] TRAXION - TRANSITIONS YOU TO A CRYPTO-READY SOCIETY
Body: TraXion signs partnership with LG CNS https://medium.com/traxion-tech/traxion-signs-partnership-with-lg-cns-74d27772108e  TraXion.tech is proud to announce that it closed an international deal with multinational electronics company LG. This partnership will see us playing a long-term and pivotal role not only in bringing LG’s business onto the blockchain but also in leading the region’s blockchain development.  LG CNS, as the information technology subsidiary of LG Group, has been leading the company into the blockchain space. Last year, they partnered with finance sector blockchain consortium R3 and became a member of the Open Blockchain Industry Association (OBCIA) in April 2018. A month later, LG launched its own blockchain service “Monachain” for the logistics industry, putting together a team of 50 people that they expect to double in the coming months.  Working with our deep expertise in Hyperledger will make it possible for LG to reap the benefits of blockchain technology without compromising on data security and privacy policies in place in its organization. While TraXion will be operating independently of Monachain, we are working with LG CNS to ensure that interoperability is foundational in all the projects we work on. This will be a challenge but we anticipate consolidation or interfacing with Monachain in the future.  This partnership deal is a key milestone in broader blockchain adoption globally. Businesses in the supply chain will be able to work more transparently and efficiently with the parties they contract with. In the long term, this will have the same inclusive and democratizing effect that the internet has brought to the business world — more opportunities for innovation, better services, and financial growth.

The goal is to fuel the growth of blockchain applications in the Philippines, targeting different areas for financial technology innovation. TraXion Hub outsources developers to different portfolio startups to collaborate, bringing down the operational cost of the member companies under manageable level and it also provides a faster way to accelerate revenue growth.  Collaboration has transformed the way software is developed. The open-source model has found vast support from developers community. New technologies like blockchain are introducing ever more reliable, transparent and accessible ways to collaborate and work on projects that matter.

Author: Artemsv
Title: [ANN] TRAXION - TRANSITIONS YOU TO A CRYPTO-READY SOCIETY
Body: TraXion Special Pre-Sale Feature    As TraXion’s Pre-sale is ongoing, one of the features this sale period offers to the purchasers, is the ability to sell their Pre-sale tokens to future purchasers on the Crowd Sale period. Through ERC721, Pre-sale token holders can split and sell their bonus tokens to a maximum of 5 people. This is called the Deed of Sale and is a unique feature of TraXion.  With the bonuses that the purchasers enjoy when buying during this particular sale period, they are provided with an option to strategically plan on how to liquidate their assets quickly. The more users and token holders that there are in the platform, the higher the value the token gains.  All in all, this feature will help promote the organic growth of TraXion’s token economy and help spread the word about the project during our pre-sale phase.  https://medium.com/traxion-tech/traxion-special-presale-feature-10e279b825b0

Author: filsid
Title: [ANN] TRAXION - TRANSITIONS YOU TO A CRYPTO-READY SOCIETY
Body: Tips For Securing Your Wallet — An Article by TraXion https://medium.com/traxion-tech/tips-for-securing-your-wallet-an-article-by-traxion-bb8ba95df9d2  Hey everyone! As we approach the start of our Pre-Sale on 05.01.18, we thought it would be good to share some tips with you on how to better secure your wallet:  *Never click on suspicious links or download apps from unknown developers. They can log your private keys and other information   from your device.  *Always be sure to back-up your wallet. Wallets usually with have an X-phrase mnemonic in case you lose your device. Write this   phrase down and store in a very secure place.  *If you are using a wallet software, always have a password for it.  *If you are using a browser for a cloud wallet such as MEW, always check to make sure you are at the correct URL address.  *Using a localized, hardware wallet such as a Trezor or a Ledger wallet can help you secure your wallet in “cold storage”. This will   help prevent your wallet from being hacked into as it will be in an offline setting.  *While on social media or forums, do not mention what cryptocurrency exchange or wallet you use.  *Do not ever share your private key for your wallet.  *If you have an online wallet, be wary of accessing your wallet on a public Wi-Fi connection as this poses a security risk.  Disclaimer: While these are some helpful tips for securing one’s wallet, there are still risks that exist and funds can be lost and or stolen. TraXion claims no responsibility for the possibility of these events occurring and this article is meant as advice. Each user should do their own research and take necessary steps for the security of their wallet.

Author: CKLA
Title: [ANN] TRAXION - TRANSITIONS YOU TO A CRYPTO-READY SOCIETY
Body: In comparison to other blockchain platforms aiming to make financial products available on a decentralized platform, we enable ALL banking and financial produ ts and services in a whitelabelled wallet.  With Hyperledger Fabric, our platform becomes enterprise-grade compared to other platforms that are still on a consumer level. This means that official and business transactions are diverse in the entire network and can be confidential between transacting parties. This very technology, with future developments in our wallet and growing, working ties with other financial services will make it easier to adapt this distributed system for all businesses.  Lastly, we are on a mission to empower and enable the unbanked and underserved. Through blockchain, the all individual participants in the blockchain will have equal opportunities and access to all services for a healthier and a more financially inclusive community.
